# MemeBro
## Design & Prototyping Sprint Document

---

## 1. Sprint Overview

**Goal:** Complete all design artifacts, wireframes, user & dev stories, risk analysis, and technical prototyping before any feature coding begins.

### 1.1 Product Summary

MemeBro is a mobile-first meme creation tool targeting Gen Alpha and Gen Z — middle schoolers through young adults. The core value proposition is speed: a meme should be shareable within seconds of the impulse to make one.

The product has four distinct functional modes:

- **Normal Mode:** Face-swap a user-uploaded photo into a pre-existing meme template. Hard requirement and primary feature.
- **Extra Roast Mode:** AI generates a brand-new meme image using only the face from the uploaded photo — no template, pure chaos, driven by user prompting.
- **Roast Mode Slider:** User fine-tunes roast intensity on a sliding scale from wholesome to unhinged.
- **Social Filter Extension:** A browser/share-sheet extension for instant meme creation directly from any image in a social media feed.

### 1.2 What This Sprint Is Not

- This is **NOT** a coding sprint. No React components, no API wiring, no full app builds.
- Quick proof-of-concept scripts (e.g., 30-line Node.js file calling a face-swap API) are allowed to validate latency and testing ONLY.

