## 4. User Stories & Dev Stories

### 4.1 User Stories — Normal Mode (Face Swapping into Existing Meme)

#### US-01 — Image Processing | Priority: High

> As a user on mobile, I want to upload a photo from my camera roll and have a face automatically detected so that I don't have to manually crop or select the face, it just works.

**Acceptance criteria:** Face bounding box appears within 1 second of image upload. Accuracy >85% on well-lit frontal faces. If detection fails, a clear inline error message explains why.

---

#### US-02 — Frontend | Priority: High

> As a user, I want to browse and select from a library of popular meme templates so that I can find the right meme format without knowing its name.

**Acceptance criteria:** Template grid loads within 1.5 seconds. At least 20 templates available at launch. Search returns results in <500ms. Templates display name and preview thumbnail.

---

#### US-03 — Image Processing | Priority: Medium

> As a user, I want to see my face composited into the selected meme template with correct proportions so that the result looks intentional, not stretched or off-center.

**Acceptance criteria:** Face is positioned in the designated face region of the template. No visible distortion on faces between 50x50px and 500x500px. Result matches template's face region bounding box within 10px.

---

#### US-04 — Image Processing | Priority: Medium

> As a Reddit or Discord user, I want the final meme to be a small enough file size to send over Discord or Reddit without looking super pixelated so that I can quickly share the image after generation without having to compress it myself.

**Acceptance criteria:** The final image must be at most 10 MB (Discord max upload size; Reddit is 20 MB). The image must not be pixelated / must be easily understood.

---

#### US-05 — API Integration | Priority: High

> As a user, I want to share the completed meme directly to my contacts or social apps so that the joke lands while everyone is still paying attention.

**Acceptance criteria:** Web Share API opens within 300ms of tapping share. Fallback clipboard copy works on all browsers. Image exports at minimum 800px width. Share works without requiring account creation.

---

#### US-06 — AI & Prompting | Priority: P0

> As a user in extra roast mode, I want to generate a completely new meme image using only my friend's face so that the meme is fresh and not limited to existing templates — maximum surprise factor.

**Acceptance criteria:** AI generation completes in <8 seconds. Prompt directs the model toward absurdist, deep-fried, or "cursed" aesthetics. Generated image embeds the uploaded face so the person is still recognizable. Output is downloadable at minimum 1024x1024px. If generation fails or triggers a safety filter, the system shows a friendly retry prompt instead of a blank screen.

---

#### US-07 — AI & Prompting | Priority: P0

> As a user in friendly roast mode, I want to generate a kind, funny meme that I could send to my grandma or school group chat so that I don't accidentally send something mean or inappropriate.

**Acceptance criteria:** Generated content passes PG-13 filter (no explicit content, slurs, or targeted harassment). Tone prompt instructs model toward affectionate humor. User can flag if result feels off.

---

#### US-10 — API Integration | Priority: P1

> As a user on a slow mobile connection, I want the app to remain usable even if the AI API is slow or unavailable so that I can still make a basic meme even when AI features are down.

**Acceptance criteria:** Normal mode (face swap) works fully offline using cached templates. Error state for AI failure shows clear message and offers normal mode as fallback. No blank screens or unhandled errors.

---

#### US-11 — Testing/CD/CI | Priority: High

> As a developer writing unit and integration tests, I want test coverage for every failure mode in the face detection pipeline, so that edge cases are caught at the unit level before they ever reach QA or production.

**Acceptance criteria:** Define five failure scenarios the unit and integration tests must cover: no face detected, low confidence, unprocessable image, timeout, and correct error message formatting. Each follow a Given/When/Then structure to ensure the detection module returns the right typed error, the service mock is never called unnecessarily, and the UI always surfaces a clean, user-facing message.

---

#### US-12 — Image Processing | Priority: Medium

> As a user uploading a group photo, I want to select which detected face should be used in the meme so that the system does not accidentally use the wrong person's face.

**Acceptance criteria:** If multiple faces are detected, the system displays a selectable thumbnail grid of detected faces within 1 second. The selected face is highlighted before processing begins. Only the selected face is passed into the face swap or AI generation pipeline.

---

#### US-13 — Image Processing | Priority: High

> As a user uploading a photo of myself, I want the face swap results to preserve my facial features accurately, so that the generated image looks realistic and recognizable.

**Acceptance criteria:** Face swap preserves key facial features and appears visually natural. Output image shows no major distortion or facial misalignment. Low-quality or unreadable uploads display a clear inline error message. Face swap processing completes within acceptable response time.

---

#### US-14 — Image Processing | Priority: Medium

> As a user, I want to be able to read any writing that is in the meme so that the joke can be understood properly.

**Acceptance criteria:** If there is any text visible and intended to be one of the foci of the image, the lettering should be recognizable and legible. There should be distinction between letters with little distortion. The text should be visible and not blend in with other parts of the image.

---

### 4.4 Dev Stories (Testable System Behaviors)

#### DS-01 — Image Processing (3 & 4) | Priority: High

> As a face detection service, I want to receive an image file and return bounding box coordinates for all detected faces so that downstream services can use precise coordinates without re-processing the image.

**Acceptance criteria:** Returns JSON with array of face objects: `{x, y, width, height, confidence}`. Empty array (not null) when no faces found. Responds in <1000ms for images. Handles JPEG, PNG, and WebP.

---

#### DS-02 — Image Processing (3 & 4) | Priority: High

> As a text generator, I want to receive text strings, font size, and coordinates and render the text with a 2px white outline on black text so that text can be legible regardless of background colors.

**Acceptance criteria:** Returns type is PNG with transparent background for compositing. Text exceeding the bounding box width auto-wraps. Text has visible outline.

---

#### DS-03 — AI & Prompting (1 & 2) | Priority: High

> As an AI prompt builder, I want to construct a prompt string from `(face_crop, mode_enum, style_seed)` inputs so that the AI model receives consistent, well-formed prompts that produce predictable output quality.

**Acceptance criteria:** Prompt includes face description, mode-specific tone instruction, and style constraints. Extra roast prompt includes chaos/absurdist instruction. Friendly roast prompt explicitly excludes profanity and mean-spirited content.

---

#### DS-04 — API Integration (7 & 8) | Priority: High

> As an API call manager, I want to enforce a 5-second timeout on all AI generation requests and return a structured error on timeout so that the UI can always show a meaningful state to the user rather than hanging indefinitely.

**Acceptance criteria:** Request times out after 5000ms with error code `TIMEOUT_ERROR`. Timeout is configurable via environment variable. Logs timestamp and duration to console.

---

#### DS-05 — API Integration | Priority: High

> As an API call manager, I want to detect and handle a 429 (Too Many Requests) response from any external API so that the app never crashes when rate limits are hit.

**Acceptance criteria:** When a 429 response is detected, the system immediately inspects for a `Retry-After` header to wait for the specified duration. The process is capped at 3 total retries.

---

#### DS-06 — API Integration | Priority: High

> As an API call manager, I want to validate the presence and format of the API key before any outbound request is made.

**Acceptance criteria:** On app initialization, the Worker checks that required environment variables are present and non-empty. If missing, throw an error with a descriptive message. This check must complete before any user-facing action is taken. Never exposes raw API key values in logs or error messages.

---

#### DS-07 — API Integration | Priority: High

> As an API routing layer on Cloudflare Workers, I want to route face-swap and AI generation requests to the appropriate external API endpoint so that each feature mode hits the correct service.

**Acceptance criteria:** A single Worker endpoint accepts a mode (face swap, roast, etc.) and routes internally to the correct API. Frontend will never call the external APIs directly.

---

#### DS-08 — API Integration | Priority: Medium

> As a Cloudflare Worker handling image upload, I want to enforce a maximum payload size of 10 MB on incoming image uploads so that the service is protected from oversized inputs.

**Acceptance criteria:** Requests with a content length exceeding 10 MB are rejected immediately with a payload too large response and error message.

---

#### DS-09 — Image Processing | Priority: High

> As a file upload validator, I want to validate image format, file size, dimensions, and image integrity before the face detection pipeline runs so that invalid or unsafe uploads do not crash the app or waste processing time.

**Acceptance criteria:** Validator accepts JPEG, PNG, WebP (if supported or convertible). Rejects unsupported formats, zero-byte files, and corrupt images. Returns structured validation errors with clear messages for the UI.

---

#### DS-10 — Image Processing (3 & 4) | Priority: High

> As the face swap processing service, I want to align and map detected facial landmarks before generating the final image, so that face swaps appear accurate and undistorted.

**Acceptance criteria:** Facial landmarks are detected before swap generation. Output face alignment matches target orientation and scale. Generated images contain no major facial distortion or stretching. Processing failures return a clear error response.

---

#### DS-11 — Image Processing (3 & 4) | Priority: High

> As the input validator, I want to have any inputs be properly uploaded and recognized, so that the user does not get frustrated with slow wait times.

**Acceptance criteria:** Any buttons in the UI are responsive and have a fast response time. Any displays that appear when a user makes an input take no more than 1 second. Displayed images that the user uploaded are in high quality and have no distortions.

---

#### DS-011 — Testing/CI/CD | Priority: High

> As a developer writing unit and integration tests, I want test coverage for both the timeout enforcement and structured error response on AI generation requests, so that regressions in timeout behavior or error formatting are caught before they reach the UI or production.

**Acceptance criteria:** Cover both the happy path and edge cases across six scenarios: validating that the timeout fires at the correct threshold, the returned error object contains all required fields with the right types, the timeout is configurable via environment variable with a safe fallback, and the console log always captures a timestamp and duration.

