## 5. Wireframes & Interaction Specs

*Domain 3 (Frontend/UX) owns this section. All pairs must put their domain's concerns regarding their research by Sunday.*

> **Think:** What specific features does each team want/need for their image/API/model work, so frontend can design accordingly?

All wireframes must be designed at **iPhone 14 dimensions (390 x 844px)** first, then show reflow at **768px (tablet)** and **1280px (desktop)**. Figma file must be shared with the full team.

### Required Screens

| Screen | Key Elements | Interaction Notes |
|--------|-------------|-------------------|
| **Home / Launch Screen** | Camera button (primary CTA), recent memes grid, mode selector pills (Normal / Extra Roast / Friendly Roast), settings icon | Mode selector persists across sessions. Recent memes grid is local cache only (no auth required for MVP). |
| **Upload / Capture Screen** | Camera viewfinder OR photo library picker, face detection overlay (bounding box on detected face), confirm / retry buttons | Face detection runs client-side on upload (MediaPipe or face-api.js). If no face detected, show inline error with suggestion. Must complete in <1 second. |
| **Template Selector** *(normal mode only)* | Scrollable grid of meme templates, search bar, trending/recent tabs, template preview on tap | Templates loaded from JSON file. Lazy-load images. Tapping a template goes directly to editor — no intermediate confirmation screen. |
| **Main Editor** | Image canvas (center, 60% of screen height), text overlay controls (tap to edit inline), model mode badge, Generate button (primary), Undo / Reset / Download buttons, text and image editing options, filters | All controls must be reachable with one thumb on mobile. No modals or popups — all editing inline on canvas. Generate triggers AI call; show skeleton loader during wait. |
| **AI Generation Loading State** | Full-screen progress indicator, estimated wait time (e.g. "~2 seconds"), cancel button, fun loading copy ("Cooking your meme...") | If API call exceeds 5 seconds, show "Taking longer than usual" message with cancel option. Log latency to console for PoC measurement. |
| **Preview & Share Screen** | Full meme preview, share button (opens native share sheet), copy link, download, start over | Share button uses Web Share API on mobile. Fallback: copy to clipboard. No login required to share. |
| **Roast Slider** | Visible slider to adjust roast mode, color goes from green to red as roast gets higher | User can adjust via mouse or keyboard buttons; should be clear and visible. |

### User-Interaction Constraints

- Max 3 taps from launch to meme ready to share in normal mode.
- Max 4 taps from launch to meme ready in roast modes (extra tap for face confirmation).
- No loading screen on app launch — home screen must render immediately from cached state.
- Touch targets minimum 44x44px (Apple HIG standard).
- All destructive actions (reset, delete) require a single confirmation — no multi-step dialogs.

### Accessibility Notes (Minimum Requirements)

- All text must be __ px big for comfortable reading *(will decide on px later, customizable)*.
- All buttons must be customized to mobile/desktop size; should not block the main view.

