## 6. Risk Analysis

| Domain | Description | Mitigation Strategy |
|--------|-------------|---------------------|
| AI & Prompting | Image generation may be too slow | Enforce a 5-second timeout, preload loading screens, cache prompts/results |
| AI & Prompting | Image generation may be inappropriate, offensive, or unsafe | Add a PG-13 prompt constraint for those 13 and younger; for those older, they have an option to opt out |
| Image Processing | Face detection may fail on blurry, tilted, dark, or group photos | Add confidence scoring, clear inline warnings, face selection UI |
| Image Processing | Face swap alignment may look distorted or low quality | Store template face region metadata and allow manual adjustment if needed |
| Image Processing | Unsupported file format input | Has specific format requirements or attempts to convert input to an accepted file format |
| Frontend / UX | Could be too cluttered / too many editing controls | Prioritize one-thumb interaction, simple design |
| Frontend / UX | Users may abandon app if meme creation takes too many taps or screens | Only 3–4 taps max and minimize confirmation dialogs |
| Security / Privacy | Uploaded faces may stay in storage | Avoid permanent storage, clear temporary files automatically, document privacy behavior |
| Testing/CI/CD | Temporary file cleanup and privacy behavior may not be validated, allowing storage bugs to reach production undetected | Write integration tests that assert uploaded files are deleted after session, no face data persists between requests, and privacy behavior is documented and regression-tested in CI on every PR |
| API Integration | API used for face swap goes down or becomes unreachable | Health-check the API on worker startup and possibly fall back to a placeholder, or disable the feature temporarily with a user message |
| API Integration | Rate limiting — external APIs return 429 under heavy usage or shared free-tier quotas | Read `Retry-After` header when present; otherwise apply exponential backoff (1s → 2s → 4s → 8s) capped at 3 retries. Return structured error so the UI can surface a clear message. |
| Image Processing | Phone uploads may include huge files, corrupt data, or unsupported formats that break face detection or expose privacy information | Run all uploads through a validator before face detection, normalize image orientation/dimensions, reject unsafe formats like SVG, and show clear retry instructions |

