## 7. Scenario-Based Tests

Scenario tests describe realistic user journeys and expected system behavior including edge cases. These are written before coding begins so developers know exactly what the system must handle.

**Format: Given / When / Then**

### 7.1 Normal Mode — Face Swap Scenarios

| Scenario | Given | Then (Expected Behavior) |
|----------|-------|--------------------------|
| Happy path — clean frontal face | User uploads a valid picture of their friend and selects the Pizza meme template. | Face is detected in <1s. Face is put into template's face region. Text is editable. Final image downloadable within 3 seconds of template selection. |
| Multiple faces in uploaded photo | User uploads a group photo with 4 faces detected. | System shows face-selection UI: thumbnail grid of detected faces. User taps one face to select. Only selected face is used for swap. |
| No face detected | User uploads a photo of a tree. | System shows inline error: "No face found — try a photo where a face is clearly visible." Upload button remains active for retry. No API call made. |
| Image too small (< 100x100px) | User uploads a tiny image. | System shows inline error: "Image too small — try a bigger photo." Rejected immediately with a pop-up window. |
| Very tilted face or blurry face | User uploads a side profile/blurry photo. | Face detection returns low confidence score. System warns user: "Face angle may affect quality — result might look off." Allows proceeding or retrying. |
| Template with no face region | Developer adds a new template missing face region metadata. | System throws `MISSING_FACE_REGION` error. Error logged. Does not crash app. |
| Dark image | User uploads image with poor lighting. | System returns low confidence score. Error thrown: "Try a photo where a face is clearly visible." |
| Obstructed image | User uploads face with hair/accessories covering parts of face. | Error thrown: "Try a photo where a face is clearly visible." |
| Meme creation from scratch | User selects "Create from scratch" instead of choosing a meme template. | System opens a blank canvas editor where the user can upload images, add text, and export the final meme. |

---

### 7.2 AI Roast Mode Scenarios

| Scenario | Given / When | Then (Expected Behavior) |
|----------|-------------|--------------------------|
| Face crop extraction | User uploads a valid image of a face for roast mode. | System extracts face crop successfully and sends cropped face to AI pipeline within 1 second. |
| Multiple faces | User uploads a group photo. | System prompts user to select which face to use before continuing. |
| Low confidence face | User uploads blurry or dark image. | System warns user that meme quality may be reduced and allows retry. |
| Face partially obstructed | User uploads an image with something covering face. | System returns low confidence warning but allows manual confirmation. |
| AI generation timeout | AI generation takes longer than 5 seconds. | System returns `{code: "TIMEOUT_ERROR", message, retryable: true}` and shows a clear retry/cancel message. |
| API rate limit hit | External AI API returns a 429 response. | System uses `Retry-After` if provided, otherwise retries with exponential backoff up to 3 times, then returns `{code: "RATE_LIMITED", message, retryable: true}`. |
| Friendly roast user prompt | User enters a custom prompt while in Friendly Roast mode. | System sanitizes the prompt and still enforces PG-13 constraints before generation. |

