### 7.3 Social Filter Extension Scenarios

| Scenario | Given / When | Then (Expected Behavior) |
|----------|-------------|--------------------------|
| Happy path — share from feed | User long-presses an image in the Instagram/X/Reddit feed and selects "Open in MemeBro" from the share sheet. | Extension launches MemeBro mini-editor in <2s with the selected image preloaded. User can pick mode without leaving the feed app. |
| Unsupported media type | User shares a link that points to a video or animated GIF. | Extension shows inline error: "MemeBro only works with static images — try a screenshot instead." Returns user to the feed without crash. |
| Cross-origin image blocked | Social platform serves the image with CORS headers that block the extension from reading pixel data. | Extension falls back to prompting "Save the image first, then open MemeBro." Logs the blocked origin for future allowlist updates. |
| No face in shared image | User shares a landscape photo or object screenshot with no human face. | Extension surfaces the same "No face found" error and offers Normal mode with a manual text-only meme as fallback. |
| Extension permission not granted | User opens the extension before granting clipboard or storage permissions. | Extension shows the permission prompt inline. If denied, it gracefully degrades to copy-link share only. |
| Large image on low-end device | Older iPhone or Android shares a 12 MB photo through the extension. | Extension downscales client-side to 1280px max edge before handing off to the main pipeline. Final exported meme stays under 10 MB. |
| postMessage timeout (background tab) | User triggers the extension, but the host tab is throttled by the OS in the background. | Extension retries postMessage handshake 3x over 2 seconds. If still no response, opens MemeBro in a new tab with the image URL attached. |
| User closes extension mid-generation | User dismisses the extension overlay while a roast-mode AI generation is still in flight. | In-flight API request is aborted via AbortController. No result is saved or rendered. No additional cost accrues beyond what was already sent. |

