## 8. Unit Tests & Edge Cases by Feature *(Team Leads Only)*

Each domain pair is responsible for writing complete unit tests for their feature area before Sprint 1 coding begins. Tests must appear in the repository with passing stubs by end of Week.

### 8.1 Face Detection Service (Domain: Image Processing)

| Test Name | Input | Expected Output |
|-----------|-------|-----------------|
| `detectFaces` returns single bounding box for one face | JPEG image with one centered frontal face | Array with one object: `{x, y, width, height, confidence}` where confidence > 0.85 |
| `detectFaces` returns multiple bboxes for group photo | JPEG image with 4 distinct faces at varying positions | Array of 4 face objects, each with unique `{x, y}` coordinates and confidence > 0.7 |
| `detectFaces` returns empty array when no face present | JPEG image of a landscape with no human faces | Empty array `[]`; not null, not undefined |
| `detectFaces` handles WebP input | WebP image with one face | Array with one face object; same schema as JPEG output |
| `detectFaces` handles PNG with alpha channel | PNG image with transparency and one face | Array with one face object; alpha channel does not affect detection accuracy |
| `detectFaces` rejects image smaller than 100x100 | JPEG image at 50x50px | Throws `InputError: "Image too small — minimum 100x100px required"` |
| `detectFaces` rejects file over 5 MB | JPEG image at 6 MB file size | Throws `InputError: "Image exceeds 5 MB size limit"` |
| `detectFaces` returns low confidence for dark image | JPEG image taken in low-light conditions with one face | Array with one face object where confidence < 0.5; consumer decides whether to warn user |
| `detectFaces` returns low confidence for side profile | JPEG image of a person turned ~70 degrees from camera | Array with one face object where confidence < 0.6 |
| `detectFaces` handles corrupt image gracefully | Binary file with .jpg extension but invalid JPEG headers | Throws `InputError: "Unable to decode image — file may be corrupt"` |
| `detectFaces` returns empty array for empty file | Zero-byte file with .png extension | Throws `InputError: "Empty file — no image data to process"` |
| `detectFaces` rejects unsupported MIME type | .bmp file upload | Throws `InputError: "Unsupported format — accepted types: JPEG, PNG, WebP"` |
| `detectFaces` responds within 1000ms | Valid JPEG image (1920x1080, 2 MB) with one face | Result returned in <1000ms (performance assertion) |
| `detectFaces` confidence is between 0 and 1 | Valid JPEG with clearly visible face | Confidence value satisfies `0 <= confidence <= 1` |
| `detectFaces` bbox stays within image bounds | JPEG (640x480) with face near the right edge | `x + width <= 640` and `y + height <= 480` for every returned face object |
| `detectFaces` bbox dimensions are positive integers | JPEG with one centered face | Width > 0 and height > 0; all coordinates are non-negative integers |

