### 8.2 AI Prompt Builder (Domain: AI & Prompting)

| Test Name | Input | Expected Output |
|-----------|-------|-----------------|
| `buildPrompt` produces chaos instruction for `extra_roast` | `{face_crop: validBlob, mode: "extra_roast", style_seed: 42}` | Prompt string contains "absurdist" or "chaotic" tone instruction and excludes PG-13 guardrails |
| `buildPrompt` produces PG-13 instruction for `friendly_roast` | `{face_crop: validBlob, mode: "friendly_roast", style_seed: 42}` | Prompt string explicitly includes "no profanity, no slurs, no targeted harassment" constraint |
| `buildPrompt` throws on invalid mode | `{face_crop: validBlob, mode: "unknown_mode", style_seed: 1}` | Throws `ValidationError: "Invalid mode — expected extra_roast or friendly_roast"` |
| `buildPrompt` keeps token count under 500 | `{face_crop: validBlob, mode: "extra_roast", style_seed: 99}` | Encoded prompt length < 500 tokens (verified via tiktoken or equivalent) |
| `buildPrompt` is deterministic for same seed | Two calls with identical `{face_crop, mode: "extra_roast", style_seed: 7}` | Both calls return the exact same prompt string |
| `buildPrompt` varies output across different seeds | `style_seed: 1` vs `style_seed: 2` | Returned prompt strings differ in at least the style/aesthetic section |
| `buildPrompt` embeds face description | `{face_crop: validBlob, mode: "friendly_roast", style_seed: 10}` | Prompt string includes a face-description segment derived from the crop (e.g., aspect ratio, orientation) |
| `buildPrompt` throws on empty face_crop | `{face_crop: null, mode: "extra_roast", style_seed: 5}` | Throws `InvalidInput: "face_crop is required"` |
| `buildPrompt` never leaks API key in output | `{face_crop: validBlob, mode: "extra_roast", style_seed: 1}` | Prompt string does not contain any substring matching the API key pattern (`sk-...`) |
| `buildPrompt` generates distinct system instructions per mode | Calls with mode `"extra_roast"` and mode `"friendly_roast"` (same crop and seed) | System-instruction segments differ; friendly includes content-policy block, extra does not |
| `buildPrompt` sanitizes user-injected text | `{face_crop, mode: "extra_roast", style_seed: 1}` with user_text containing prompt-injection attempt | User text is escaped or placed in a quoted literal block — never executed as a prompt directive |
| `buildPrompt` friendly_roast rejects banned keywords | `{face_crop, mode: "friendly_roast", style_seed: 3}` combined with user text containing slur | Throws `ContentPolicyError: "Input contains disallowed language"` |

