### 8.4 API Call Manager (Domain: API Integration)

| Test Name | Input | Expected Output |
|-----------|-------|-----------------|
| `callAI` times out after 5 seconds | AI generation request that hangs (mock never resolves) | Returns `{code: "TIMEOUT_ERROR", message: "Request timed out after 5000ms", retryable: true}` |
| `callAI` respects Retry-After header on 429 | Mock returns 429 with `Retry-After: 3` header | Manager waits 3 seconds then retries; second call succeeds and returns the AI result |
| `callAI` uses exponential backoff without Retry-After | Mock returns 429 with no `Retry-After` header | Retries at ~1s, ~2s, ~4s intervals; if all fail returns `{code: "RATE_LIMITED", retryable: true}` |
| `callAI` caps retry attempts at 3 | Mock returns 429 on every attempt | After 3 retries (4 total calls), returns `{code: "RATE_LIMITED", message: "Rate limit exceeded after 3 retries", retryable: true}` |
| `callAI` validates API key on init | Environment with `OPENAI_API_KEY` unset or empty | Throws `ConfigError: "Missing required environment variable: OPENAI_API_KEY"` |
| `callAI` rejects payload over 10 MB | Image upload request with 12 MB body | Returns HTTP 413 with `{code: "PAYLOAD_TOO_LARGE", message: "Maximum upload size is 10 MB"}` |
| `callAI` routes face_swap mode to face-swap endpoint | `{mode: "face_swap", image: blob}` | Request sent to the face-swap API path (e.g., `/api/face-swap`), not the generation endpoint |
| `callAI` routes extra_roast mode to image-gen endpoint | `{mode: "extra_roast", face_crop: blob, prompt: "..."}` | Request sent to the image-generation API path (e.g., `/api/image`) |
| `callAI` never exposes API key in error messages | Mock returns 500 server error | Error object's message field does not contain the API key substring; console.error log also clean |
| `callAI` returns retryable true for 5xx errors | Mock returns HTTP 502 Bad Gateway | Returns `{code: "SERVER_ERROR", message: "...", retryable: true}` |
| `callAI` returns retryable false for non-429 4xx errors | Mock returns HTTP 400 Bad Request | Returns `{code: "CLIENT_ERROR", message: "...", retryable: false}` |
| `callAI` abort cancels in-flight request | `AbortController.abort()` called 1 second into a 5-second request | Request is cancelled; no result or error is returned; fetch was aborted |
| `callAI` timeout is configurable via env var | `AI_TIMEOUT_MS` env var set to 3000 | Request times out after 3000ms instead of default 5000ms |
| `callAI` logs timestamp and duration | Successful AI generation request completing in 2.3 seconds | Console.log output includes ISO timestamp and "duration: 2300ms" |
| `callAI` concurrent requests have independent retry counters | Two simultaneous requests; first gets 429, second succeeds | First request retries independently; second request returns immediately without delay |
| `callAI` handles concurrent requests with independent retry logic | Two simultaneous calls — first with a transient network error injected, second with a valid input | First request retries independently; second request returns immediately without delay |

